sections.title: How the population has changed in St. Helens
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, St. Helens was the 17th largest local authority in the North West, with a total population of 181,095. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the North West, 2002-2020
Population density in St. Helens
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in St. Helens was 1,328 people per square kilometre, which was more than the North West (522), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the North West, 2020
Median age in St. Helens
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in St. Helens was 43 years, which was older than the North West (40 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
